Debug Document

Bug ID: (e.g., #04 - Coffee Machine Reset)
Status: (Open / In Progress / Resolved)
Reporter: (Who found it?)
Description: What actually happened? (e.g., "The green circle disappeared but the machine didn't turn blue.")
Steps to Reproduce:
    Start the game.
    Click the coffee machine.
    Quickly drag to the customer before the timer hits 100%.
Expected Result: Machine remains in 'Producing' state.
Actual Result: Machine resets to 'Void'.

Bug ID: #01 - Click VS Drag Conflict
Status: Open
Reporter: Kyaw Sis Thway
Description: The logic currently used for mouse operation has a major problem. 
                It cannot distinguish between drag and click. After the introduction of isClicker type entity,
                their dual functions are in conflict according to current logic. BreadPlate can be clicked three times and the outline
                color will change according to how many times it has been clicked. But now, it can only be clicked once and the later
                result all become drag mechanic.
Steps to Reproduce:
    Start the game.
    Drag LoafOfBread from BreadBasket to BreadPlate.
    Click BreadPlate once.
    Click again.
Expected Result: The color of the outline doesn't change from yellow to orange, which is the second stage representing two slices.
Actual Result:  The color remains yellow. Drag SliceOfBread to SandwichPlate. The yellow outline becomes transparent proving
                that its count is now 0.